==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exode
<hw>Ex"ode</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>exodium</ets>,
Gr. <?/ (sc. <?/ song) fr. <?/ belonging to an exit, or to the finale of
a tragedy, fr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>exode</ets>. See <er>Exodus</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Departure; exodus; esp., the exodus of the Israelites
from Egypt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>L. Coleman.</au>
<au>Bolingbroke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gr. Drama)</fld> <def>The final chorus; the
catastrophe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An afterpiece of a comic
description, either a farce or a travesty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exodic</ent>⟦br⟧
